definition:
A man of the tribe of Levi living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at Exo.6.21; 
 son of: Izhar (H3324); 
 brother of: Korah (H7141I), Zichri (H2147) and Shelomith (H8019A)
 § Nepheg = "sprout"
1) one of sons of Izhar and grandson of Kohath of the tribe of Levi in the time of the exodus
2) one of the sons of David born to him at Jerusalem
